In HTML5, changes of the orientation and acceleration of a device can be monitored with the help of <code>deviceorientation</code> and <code>devicemotion</code> events. W3C has published the [http://www.w3.org/TR/orientation-event/ DeviceOrientation Event Specification]. In the Mozialla Developer Network, see the event reference for [https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Reference/Events/deviceorientation deviceorientation] and [https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Reference/Events/devicemotion devicemotion]. Apple developers should consult the [https://developer.apple.com/library/safari/documentation/SafariDOMAdditions/Reference/DeviceOrientationEventClassRef/DeviceOrientationEvent/DeviceOrientationEvent.html DeviceOrientationEvent] and the [https://developer.apple.com/library/safari/documentation/SafariDOMAdditions/Reference/DeviceMotionEventClassRef/DeviceMotionEvent/DeviceMotionEvent.html DeviceMotionEvent] class reference in Apple's Safari Developer Library.




