{{Documentation subpage}}
<!-- PLEASE ADD CATEGORIES AND INTERWIKIS AT THE BOTTOM OF THIS PAGE -->

This template is a combination of {{tl|frac}} and {{tl|sort}}. It allows numerical sorting of a column containing fractions. 

== Examples ==
*{{xpd|sortfrac|78|2|3}}
*{{xpd|sortfrac|2|3}}
*{{xpd|sortfrac|3}}

For examples of tables using the template see [[DHL Delivery Man Award]].

== Code ==

<source lang=html5>
<span class="template-frac">
{{#if:{{{3|}}}
   |{{sort
     |{{#expr: {{{1}}}+{{{2}}}/{{{3}}} }}
     |{{{1}}}<sup>{{{2}}}</sup>&frasl;<sub>{{{3}}}</sub>}}
   |{{#if:{{{2|}}}
     |{{sort
       |{{#expr: {{{1}}}/{{{2}}} }}
       |<sup>{{{1}}}</sup>&frasl;<sub>{{{2}}}</sub>}}
     |{{sort
       |{{#expr: 1/{{{1}}} }}
       |<sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>{{{1}}}</sub>}}
    }}
}}
</span>
</source>

==See also==
* [[Template:Sortname]] - sort names using "last name, first name" as default sort key
* [[Template:Autotable5]] - generate a sortable table with auto-numbered rows, up to 5 columns

